  "metadata": [
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Summary"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The project involves maintenance dredging of the Calumet-Sag Channel and the Little Calumet River in Illinois. The dredged materials, which are polluted, will be disposed of in land disposal areas, specifically the Lucas-Berg Pit in Worth, Illinois. This is part of a federal effort to maintain the waterway for commercial traffic. There were concerns about potential groundwater contamination from the disposal site, leading to plans for an impervious clay liner to prevent pollution. The project aims to ensure safe disposal while addressing environmental concerns, particularly groundwater protection."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Themes"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "Water Systems"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
