        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Key People"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "U.S. Army Engineer District, Chicago",
          "Illinois Environmental Protection Agency (IEPA)",
          "Metropolitan Sanitary District of Greater Chicago (MSDGC)",
          "Village of Worth"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The maintenance dredging of the Calumet-Sag Channel was proposed to ensure the waterway remains navigable for commercial traffic, which is vital for local economies. Public concerns arose regarding the potential contamination of groundwater from the disposal of polluted dredged materials, prompting the inclusion of an impervious clay liner in the plans to mitigate environmental risks. Ultimately, the project aimed to balance the need for infrastructure maintenance with environmental protection measures."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
